---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import AccordionComponent from "../../components/Accordion.astro";
---

<Layout title="Accordion">
	<div class="container">
		<section class="section">
			<p>The Accordion component creates collapsible content sections that help organize information in a space-efficient way. Perfect for FAQs, content sections, and any scenario where you need to show/hide content on demand.</p>
			
			<h2>Demo</h2>
			<div class="component-demo">
				<AccordionComponent header="What is an Accordion?">
					<p>An accordion is a UI component that allows users to toggle the visibility of content sections. It's commonly used for FAQs, menu items, and organizing large amounts of content in a compact space.</p>
				</AccordionComponent>

				<AccordionComponent header="How to Use">
					<p>Simply wrap your content in the Accordion component and provide a header prop. The component will handle the expand/collapse functionality automatically.</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Add a descriptive header</li>
						<li>Include any content inside the component</li>
						<li>Users can click to expand/collapse</li>
					</ul>
				</AccordionComponent>

				<AccordionComponent header="Features">
					<p>The accordion component includes:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Smooth animations</li>
						<li>Keyboard accessibility</li>
						<li>Responsive design</li>
						<li>Customizable styling</li>
					</ul>
					<img src="https://placehold.co/400x200" alt="Accordion features illustration">
				</AccordionComponent>

				<AccordionComponent header="Technical Details">
					<p>Built with semantic HTML and enhanced with JavaScript for smooth interactions. Uses CSS transitions for animations and follows WCAG accessibility guidelines.</p>
				</AccordionComponent>
			</div>

			<h3>Usage Example</h3>
			<pre><code>&lt;AccordionComponent header="Your Header Text"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Your content goes here&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/AccordionComponent&gt;</code></pre>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>